rComments: Looking back to the 2006 class, as a person halfway through my dissertation in philosophy, this course was probably one of the most important courses I ever took. Converted me to German philosophy and that Secularism could be a topic of study. The texts he used formed the backbone of what I would do later. Thanks from the future Prof. Pollock!

Readings were great.  Lectures were insightful.  Class discussion, however, was painful and 9am on a Friday morning left much to be desired.  But, for the most part, a good experience.  I'd take another class of Pollock's.

crazy work load and badass marker. but he's fair and gives back as much as he asks for. you'll learn something, a good mark will be hugely satisfying and...well...he's one helluva nice guy! PS: he rocks the 80's style jeans and sneakers combo like nobodies business.
